Description: Ostracon, remains of the body of a red-grey pottery vessel, the fabric is relatively coarse and contains many small white inclusions, the exterior is covered with a pale red-brown slip and faint traces of four lines of black-painted demotic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393892) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393892)
